{
  "text": "The execution of a distributed join can be broadly decomposed into an initial data redistribution stage followed by a local join process [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . This latter process has been extensively studied and its cost does not contain any intermachine communication. For the purpose of this work, we focus on the former phase.",
